Female (paratype). Total length 1.55; carapace 0.73 length, 0.61 width; abdomen 0.82 length, 0.59 width. Habitus as in Fig. 11A, C, E. As in male except as noted. Carapace: without any pattern. Mouthparts: chelicerae and endites unmodified. Abdomen: dorsal scutum well sclerotized, postepigastric scutum boat-shaped, very narrow. Genitalia: anterior margin of the postepigastric scutum slightly sclerotized, behind the anterior margin is a depression (dp); the winding tube runs posteriorly (wt), ending in a bowl-shaped atrium (bsa) (Fig. 11
